## Mode 2 — "Note Runner" design contract (frozen for S08)

| Aspect | Decision |
|---|---|
| Metaphor | Chrome-dino side-scroller; ground line at bottom, hit-line fixed near left-third |
| Motion | Notes spawn at right, scroll left at `pxPerSec`; staff lines scroll with them |
| Goal | Tap the correct piano key as the note crosses the **hit-line** (pitch + timing) |
| Duration | Each note carries `beats`; spacing between notes = `beats × beatPx` |
| Hit window | ±140 ms around hit-line crossing → on-beat; outside = miss (stumble) |
| Avatar | Runs in place at hit-line; **hops** on correct (dino jump), **stumbles** on miss |
| Melodies | Real tunes from `melodyLibrary`; song title shown; notes follow the song's key |
| Adaptive speed | After a clean phrase (e.g. 8 notes, 0 misses) → ramp `pxPerSec` +15%, show banner |
| Encouragement | Banner "Nice! Let's try faster 🚀" 1.2 s before ramp; never punishes silently |
| Lives | 3 misses → gameover (consistent with Mode 1) |
| Scoring | +10 on-beat × streak multiplier; perfect-phrase bonus +50 |

## Children's melodies (frozen note data, C-major friendly)

Format per note: `{ name, beats }` — `beats` in quarter units (1=quarter, 2=half, 0.5=eighth).
Executor maps `name`→midi via existing note utils.

- **Twinkle Twinkle:** C C G G | A A G(2) | F F E E | D D C(2)
- **Mary Had a Little Lamb:** E D C D | E E E(2) | D D D(2) | E G G(2)
- **Jingle Bells (chorus):** E E E(2) | E E E(2) | E G C D | E(4)
- **Happy Birthday:** G(.5) G(.5) A G C | B(2) | G(.5) G(.5) A G D | C(2)
- **Ode to Joy:** E E F G | G F E D | C C D E | E(1.5) D(.5) D(2)

## Definition of Done
- Mascot exposes ≥ 7 emotions with visibly distinct face + body motion; used across screens.
- Ground shadow is a separate element; shrinks/fades as mascot lifts (no jump-with-body).
- Mode 2 playable end-to-end: pick a melody, staff scrolls, avatar hops, song is recognisable.
- Speed ramps only after clean play, with the warning banner; gameover at 3 misses.
- Mode 1 (Find) behaviour identical to pre-S08 (regression-safe).
- All new code meets `../CODE-QUALITY.md` (piano-keyboard-export bar): typed, `memo`+`displayName`,
  cleaned-up tweens/RAF, named constants, a11y, JSDoc on public APIs.
- `git commit` after every task (Git Discipline).

## Out of scope (→ S09)
- Landscape 667×375 audit + responsive fixes + piano compaction.
- Final cross-device QA and README modes/character section.

## Risks
- Scroll perf: drive staff scroll via one GSAP/RAF transform, not per-note React state.
- Audio timing vs visual hit-line: tie audio trigger to the same crossing event.
- Melody→midi mapping must respect existing pool/util naming (no new note system).
